Author: Bryan Jimenez

mycipher is an S-DES (Simplified Data Encryption Standard) encryptor/decryptor


To compile:

	unzip
	make  

To run:

	mycipher [-d] <key> <init_vector> <input_file> <output_file>

Notes:

	files will be read/written one line at a time expecting/printing one word at each line

Thanks to:

	(Algorithm)
	http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Block_cipher_modes_of_operation

	(binary hex decimal)
	ghex hex editor
	
	(decimal/ascii to binary)
	http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5369440/how-does-one-convert-ascii-to-binary
